2.4. Discharge Product in Hybrid Na–Air Battery
To address the issues related with undecomposed discharge
products, poor round trip efficiency and cost associated with
organic electrolytes, mixed electrolyte systems have been pro-
posed. The mixed electrolyte, commonly known as hybrid
electrolyte, implies a separation of the electrolytes into two
compartments in the cell with a solid electrolyte membrane
blocking oxygen and water diffusion but transporting cations.
